title: Panic using rocket-include-static-resources on nightly rust

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
### Code ```Rust #![feature(proc_macro_hygiene, decl_macro)] #[macro_use] extern crate rocket; #[macro_use] extern crate rocket_include_static_resources; use rocket_include_static_resources::StaticResponse; #[get("/favicon.ico")] fn favicon() -> StaticResponse { static_response!("static/favicon.ico") } #[get("//")] fn hello(name: String, age: u8) -> String { format!("Hello, {} year old named {}!", age, name) } fn main() { rocket::ignite().mount("/hello", routes![hello]).launch(); } ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.53.0-nightly (07e0e2ec2 2021-03-24) binary: rustc commit-hash: 07e0e2ec268c140e607e1ac7f49f145612d0f597 commit-date: 2021-03-24 host: x86_64-pc-windows-msvc release: 1.53.0-nightly LLVM version: 12.0.0 ``` ### Error output ``` Compiling spaceengi v0.1.0 (C:\Users\Casey\OneDrive\Scripts\spaceengi) thread 'rustc' panicked at 'found unstable fingerprints for predicates_of(core[f48f]::fmt::Display): GenericPredicates { parent: None, predicates: [(Binder(TraitPredicate()), C:\Users\Casey\.rustup\toolchains\nightly-x86_64-pc-windows-msvc\lib/rustlib/src/rust\library\core\src\fmt\mod.rs:642:1: 642:18 (#0))] }', /rustc/07e0e2ec268c140e607e1ac7f49f145612d0f597\compiler\rustc_query_system\src\query\plumbing.rs:593:5 ```
